// Example parameter file for infra/azure/main.bicep.
//
// COPY this to a NON-committed file (e.g. main.dev.bicepparam) before
// deploying. The .gitignore at the repo root excludes
// *.bicepparam EXCEPT main.bicepparam.example.
//
// To deploy:
//   1. Pre-create the resource group:
//        az group create -n movate-dev-rg -l eastus2
//   2. Pre-populate Key Vault secrets (chicken-and-egg note below).
//   3. Run the deployment with this param file:
//        az deployment group create \
//            -g movate-dev-rg \
//            -f infra/azure/main.bicep \
//            -p main.dev.bicepparam
//
// Chicken-and-egg note: the deployment provisions Key Vault, but the
// Container Apps reference secrets that must exist in KV at deploy
// time. Two options:
//   A. Two-pass deploy: first pass creates KV + Postgres + ACR + Logs;
//      operator populates secrets; second pass deploys the Container
//      Apps. Cleaner but more steps.
//   B. Pre-create KV by hand, then run the full deploy (Bicep is
//      idempotent on KV).
// Stage 2 (`movate deploy` CLI) automates option A.

using './main.bicep'

// REQUIRED — these have no defaults.
param env = 'dev'
param image = 'movate:0.5.0'

// First-pass deploys (env never deployed before): set to FALSE so the
// Container Apps don't try to resolve KV secrets that don't exist yet.
// Provision infra → populate KV secrets → flip this to TRUE → re-run
// the deployment. After that, leave it true.
param enableApiWorker = false

// REQUIRED — sourced from Key Vault using `getSecret`. Replace the
// vault name + secret name with your real values. Or for a one-off
// dev deploy you can pass a literal; just NEVER commit a literal.
//
// Example using a Key Vault reference (recommended):
//
//   param postgresAdminPassword = az.getSecret(
//     '<subscriptionId>',
//     'movate-bootstrap-rg',     // RG that holds the bootstrap KV
//     'movate-bootstrap-kv',     // name of the bootstrap KV
//     'pg-admin-password'        // secret name
//   )
//
// Replace this dummy literal before deploying for real:
param postgresAdminPassword = 'ReplaceMeBeforeDeployment-ChangeMe!'

// OPTIONAL — defaults to resourceGroup().location if omitted.
param location = 'eastus2'

// OPTIONAL but STRONGLY RECOMMENDED — short suffix (2-6 alphanumeric
// chars) appended to globally-unique resource names. Key Vault, ACR,
// and Postgres Flex names live in Azure-wide namespaces, so vanilla
// `movate-dev-kv` etc. are likely already claimed by another tenant.
// Pick an org slug or your initials. RG-scoped resources (logs, ACA
// env, ACA apps) ignore this — they only have to be RG-unique.
//
// Example: nameSuffix = 'mvio' → KV becomes 'movate-dev-kv-mvio',
// ACR becomes 'movatedevacrmvio'.
param nameSuffix = ''

// OPTIONAL — common tags. Add your own as needed (cost center, owner, ...).
param tags = {
  application: 'movate'
  environment: 'dev'
  managedBy: 'bicep'
  owner: 'platform-team'
}

// OPTIONAL — comma-separated allow-list of browser origins for CORS.
// Becomes MDK_CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS on the API container. Empty string
// disables browser callers (server-to-server calls still work). When
// onboarding a new Angular front end, add its origin here and re-run
// `az deployment group create` — idempotent in one apply (no more
// post-deploy `az containerapp update` step).
//
// Example for the Friday Mova iO demo:
//   param corsAllowedOrigins = 'http://localhost:4200,https://mova-io.movate.com'
param corsAllowedOrigins = ''

// OPTIONAL — cold-start knobs. Override the API / worker
// `scale.minReplicas`. Leave at the -1 sentinel (the param default) to
// keep the per-env defaults (dev/staging = 1, prod = 2) — i.e. no change
// to today's scaling. Set to 0 to allow scale-to-zero (cheapest; the
// first request / queued job after idle pays a cold start, which can
// time out a tight `GET /healthz` probe). Set to 1+ to keep a replica
// always-warm for QA/prod so no request ever pays the cold start.
//
//   param apiMinReplicas = 1      // always-warm API (no /healthz cold-start)
//   param workerMinReplicas = 1   // always-warm worker
// param apiMinReplicas = -1
// param workerMinReplicas = -1
